Tony Robinson presents aerial footage of areas of Britain that are off limits to the public, including a shipyard in Scotland where aircraft carriers are built and a shipwreck on the Kent coast that is filled with explosives. Plus, a gated community with a dark past, James Dyson's top-secret research laboratory, and a platform in the sea inhabited by people who wish to become an independent nation.(n)

Plus, a self-confessed `crazy cat lady' brings in a ginger tom which urgently needs leg surgery. Last in the series.(n)

programme.desc: The trauma team at St George's Hospital in south-west London fights to save the life of a young woman involved in a motorbike accident, which has completely severed her right leg below the knee. An 11-year-old boy is brought in after having a prolonged epileptic seizure, and a 19-year-old arrives with a sewing needle stuck in her foot, but she seems more keen on taking advice from her mum in Bulgaria than from the doctor.(n)

programme.title: Too Posh to Parent
programme.desc: From etiquette lessons to professional potty trainers who guarantee results in three days, modern parents have never had so many experts to choose from - if they can afford it. This documentary follows the people who provide a wide range of childcare services to the wealthy, as well as the families that employ them, from 34-year-old Nina Naustdal and her household of full-time staff, to family concierge Lucy Challenger, who is on a mission to find a client a nanny who can both cook vegan food and ski.(n)

programme.title: Naked Attraction

In the first edition, Aina, a music producer from London, wants to find someone adventurous who she can have a deeper connection with, while Guildford-based designer Mal - who has dated men and women - is curious to see who she will be drawn to when all options are laid bare before her.(n)

Joining regular panellist Alan Davies are comedienne Sara Pascoe, Bad Education and Fresh Meat star Jack Whitehall, and stand-up and The Last Leg host Adam Hills.(n)

programme.title: Exhibition
programme.desc: Premiere. An artistic couple who have lost the ability to communicate with each other decide to sell the modernist house they have lived and worked in for 20 years. As the awkward process of finding a buyer unfolds, it brings the anxieties both have been repressing about their relationship bubbling to the surface. Drama, starring Viv Albertine, Liam Gillick and Tom Hiddleston.(n)

programme.title: Frenzy
programme.desc: London is terrorised by a serial killer who strangles women with his tie. When two of the victims are found to be the ex-wife and girlfriend of the same man, the police incorrectly suspect him of the crime. Aided by his friends, he goes on the run from the law in an attempt to prove his innocence. Alfred Hitchcock's thriller, starring Jon Finch and Barry Foster.(n)

programme.title: White Elephant
programme.desc: A priest uses his political connections to get a hospital built in the slums of Buenos Aires, but his work is disrupted by corrupt authorities and conflict between rival drug gangs, which is steadily reaching all-out war. A second clergyman joins him in his work, but the new arrival's faith has been challenged by tragedy. Drama, starring Ricardo Darin, Jeremie Renier and Martina Gusman. In Spanish.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: The A to Z of TV Gardening
programme.desc: Carol Kirkwood looks at subjects beginning with the letter G, continuing her alphabetical journey through the world of horticulture. Along the way, she gets inspiration and advice from some of the BBC's most popular gardening presenters.(n)

programme.title: Glorious Gardens from Above
programme.desc: Horticulturist Christine Walkden visits Essex, where she experiments with triangular planting and has tea and cake at Beth Chatto Gardens. Plus, at RHS Hyde Hall she moves rocks with a former student, and then sails across the Thames to the Blackwater Estuary.(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: Monty Don is at Longmeadow giving advice on how to deal with unruly roses, taking cuttings of herbs and planting a new tree, and Carol Klein continues her series on plant families, exploring some of the most popular relations of the rose. Nick Macer is in London visiting a town garden where two different microclimates offer very different planting opportunities, Adam Frost reveals his plans for his new garden, while Flo Headlam is in the heart of Bristol, transforming unpromising grey spaces into vibrant green ones.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Reports on harvest time around the UK. Anita Rani picks peppermint to make cocktails, while Matt Baker discovers how harvesting has changed over the years at the Gaddesden Estate, and John Craven gathers cobnuts. Plus, Joe Crowley investigates how many of the farm brands on sale in supermarkets actually come from a farm, and Adam Henson celebrates 40 years of One Man and His Dog.(n)

programme.title: The Beechgrove Garden
programme.desc: The presenters unveil a sparkling summer bedding display, Carole Baxter shows off some colourful calla lilies and black-eyed Susans, and it is tasting time for Jim McColl's tomatoes. Chris Beardshaw dons his waders to plant in the pond and Jim pays his second visit to Tillycoultry allotments, where he looks at the communal greenhouses and finds out about the tuition sessions in a range of garden machinery.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Best Bites
programme.desc: John Torode selects his favourite moments and recipes from the series.(n)

programme.title: Lorraine Pascale: How to Be a Better Cook
programme.desc: Sally Mack lacks the confidence to cook for anyone except herself, but after turning 50 she decided that had to change. Lorraine creates a Chinese-inspired menu of dishes that are simple to prepare, including sweet-and-sour ribs, chicken and cashew nut stir fry and a showstopping cake. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: MOTD2 Extra
programme.desc: Mark Chapman presents football discussion with the Match of the Day team, focusing on the headlines from yesterday's matches and news ahead of today's fixtures.(n)

programme.title: Hairy Bikers' Best of British
programme.desc: Si King and Dave Myers explore the history of the Vegetarian Society and discover how the movement changed public attitudes and became part of the mainstream. They also consider how British gardening has influenced the nation's cuisine, and provide a few recipes along the way.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The South West competitors Chris Wheeler, Jude Kereama and Josh Eggleton prepare main courses as they compete to be crowned champion. The chefs serve up meals including a dish celebrating different cuts of beef, sweet breads in marmite and maple syrup, and a take on cottage pie featuring Asian flavours.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: South West chefs Jude Kereama, Josh Eggleton and Chris Wheeler continue the battle to cook at a banquet held at the Palace of Westminster celebrating ordinary Britons honoured by the Queen. As each of them prepare their desserts, they will all be out to impress as only two can make it through to tomorrow's regional final.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The two remaining South West chefs cook their entire menus again for judges Prue Leith, Oliver Peyton and Matthew Fort. The arbitrators are joined by journalist and restaurant critic Grace Dent, who helps them decide which budding chef will go forward to the national finals.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Anita Manning and Adam Patridge search for collectibles at Crathes Castle in Aberdeenshire, but it is Paul Martin who seems to scoop a big prize when he spots a valuable 19th-century oriental armrest. The presenter also learns about the area's shipbuilding past.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: Photographer Vianet Djenguet travels to The Republic of Congo, the country he was born in, to document the incredible environments and wildlife. His journey stretches from the coastline to rainforests untouched by human development, and includes encounters with animals including chimpanzees, forest elephants and lowland gorillas.(n)

programme.title: The Story of Are You Being Served
programme.desc: The cast, crew and writers of the much-loved TV classic about a department store look back on its 13-year run. At its peak, the sitcom - inspired by writer Jeremy Lloyd's time working at former London store Simpsons - attracted up to 22 million viewers. Alexander Armstrong narrates.(n)

programme.title: Athletics
programme.desc: Ore Oduba presents action from the half-marathon that ran from Newcastle upon Tyne to South Shields, as Mo Farah attempted to retain his title in the men's elite race.(n)

programme.title: New York: America's Busiest City
programme.desc: Anita Rani, Ade Adepitan, Ant Anstead and Dan Snow look at food consumption in the Big Apple. From dusk until dawn at the New Fulton fish market in The Bronx, they uncover the hidden night time operations, hard-nosed negotiations and price fluctuations of this enormous wholesale operation. Ade also looks into local apple production, Anita visits a cattle farm that supplies the region's steakhouses, Ant visits the New NY Bridge, and Dan heads to Freshkills on Staten Island. Once the world's biggest landfill, it's been transformed into 2,200 acres of parkland.(n)

programme.title: Scotland and the Battle for Britain
programme.desc: Andrew Marr presents a two-part programme exploring the transformation of Scottish politics in recent years. The first programme looks back over the shift in power that has occurred since the 1950s, with the Unionists losing ground to Labour, who have ultimately given way to the SNP. With contributions from leading political figures including Nicola Sturgeon, Alex Salmond and Tony Blair.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Jimmy Carr and the Science of Laughter - A Horizon Special.
programme.desc: The comedian takes over the science programme in a special episode for BBC's sitcom season, turning it into a chat show with eminent scientists as guests. He talks to them about the nature of laughter, with the studio audiences serving as guinea pigs in his attempt to get to the bottom of what laughter is, what it has to do with comedy, and why human beings find it a pleasurable sensation. The programme reveals that laughter predates the human species and may have played a vital role in our evolution.(n)

programme.title: Fleabag
programme.desc: Claire takes Fleabag to an all-female silent retreat. What should be a period of peaceful solitude is disrupted by some explosive secrets coming to light, a surprising connection with an old acquaintance, and an unusual neighbouring workshop. Comedy, written by and starring Phoebe Waller-Bridge.(n)

programme.title: Murder in Successville
programme.desc: George Shelley helps Sleet solve the murder of computer hacker Ed Sheeran. Forensics officer Angela Merkel is convinced that he was killed for breaking into the personal files of some very powerful people, and a banker, an arms dealer and a technology entrepreneur are likely suspects - but Sleet is more concerned that the case does not get in the way of his own plans to launch a new app.(n)

programme.title: Absolutely Fashion: Inside British Vogue
programme.desc: For the first time in British Vogue's 100-year history, TV cameras have been allowed to film behind closed doors, granting documentary maker Richard Macer unprecedented access to the UK's style bible, its cover stars, designers, and those who run it, as the magazine prepares to celebrate its centenary. In the first of two programmes, editor-in-chief Alexandra Shulman decides she wants to change the magazine's front covers to appeal to a younger audience - the Instagram generation. Will this new relaxed style work for British Vogue?.(n)

programme.title: The Genius of Turner: Painting the Industrial Revolution
programme.desc: Docu-drama revealing there is more to painter JMW Turner than his famous landscapes, examining key paintings incorporating machines, science and technology that reflect the scientific and industrial revolutions he lived through. Including interviews with historian Simon Schama and artist Tracey Emin. Narrated by Samuel West, with Thomas Coombes portraying Turner.(n)

programme.title: Clydebuilt: The Ships That Made the Commonwealth
programme.desc: The repair ship CS Mackay-Bennett was launched in 1884 and helped keep information flowing along a network of underwater cables that connected Britain with its Empire and the world, but was also used to recover bodies of those who died when the Titanic sank. David Hayman travels to Halifax, Nova Scotia, to investigate the story of the vessel and learns of a DNA mystery that has taken more than a century to solve.(n)

programme.title: Beck
programme.desc: An investigative journalist is found murdered in his own home, and the fingerprints of a notorious criminal debt collector are found at the scene of the crime. More suspects enter the frame when it becomes clear the man was being threatened by right-wing extremists, but when the victim's work on a book about `society's dark side' emerges, the case takes an unexpected turn. Suddenly, there is much more at stake than finding the journalist's killer, and Beck and his team find themselves struggling to protect the balance of their professional and private lives. Crime thriller, starring Peter Haber. In Swedish.(n)

programme.title: Duets: The Andy Williams Show
programme.desc: A selection of the veteran performer's favourite duets recorded during his decade-long run as host of a weekly variety show on the American network NBC. Featuring Bing Crosby, Ray Charles, Johnny Mathis and Ella Fitzgerald, as well as Judy Garland singing Somewhere Over the Rainbow, and Ray Charles with What'd I Say.(n)

programme.title: Burt Bacharach: A Life in Song
programme.desc: Coverage of a unique concert staged at London's Royal Festival Hall celebrating the music of songwriter and performer Burt Bacharach. Some of his most famous songs are performed by artists including Alfie Boe, Sophie Ellis-Bextor, Shaun Escoffery, Rebecca Ferguson, Justin Hayward, Michael Kiwanuka, Laura Mvula and Joss Stone. Burt himself also performs, accompanied by his band, and chats to Michael Grade about the art of songwriting and shares the stories behind some of his best-loved hits.(n)

programme.title: Easy Listening Hits at the BBC
programme.desc: Archive performances by some of the best-known easy-listening musicians of the 1960s and 70s, including Sergio Mendes & Brasil 66, Burt Bacharach, the Carpenters and Andy Williams.(n)

programme.desc: A selection of performances from the long-running chart show.(n)

programme.title: From Andy Pandy to Zebedee: The Golden Age of Children's TV
programme.desc: The story of the struggle to deliver television programmes for children, who were an often overlooked audience in the days before everything went digital. Includes interviews with pioneers of children's TV, such as Bernard Cribbins, Derek Griffiths, Janet Ellis, Johnny Ball and John Craven. Narrated by Nigel Planer.(n)

programme.title: Madness on Wheels: Rallying's Craziest Years
programme.desc: The evolution of the motorsport in the 1980s, which saw the relaxation of rules and the emergence of the Group B era. Hugely powerful vehicles including the Peugeot 205 T16, Ford RS200, Lancia Delta S4, Audi Quattro S1 and MG Metro 6R4 reached higher speeds than ever before, creating a surge in the sport's popularity - but also posing an enormous risk to spectators. With contributions by former world champions Ari Vatanen, Walter Roehrl and Stig Blomqvist, plus driver Michele Mouton, ex-Lancia team manager Cesare Fiorio and current FIA president Jean Todt.(n)

programme.title: The Comet's Tale
programme.desc: The story of man's understanding of comets, once thought to signal impending doom, revealing how space missions have provided important information on what they are made of, where they come from, and how they can influence events on Earth.(n)

programme.title: The Sky at Night
programme.sub-title: Interstellar: The Journey to Proxima B.
programme.desc: Chris Lintott and Maggie Aderin-Pocock report on the recent discovery of a planet with similar qualities to Earth orbiting Proxima Centauri, the nearest star to our solar system. The programme examines what the environment of this world might be like and the logistics of building a spacecraft capable of travelling 4.23 light years to reach it.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Horizon: How Big Is the Universe?.
programme.desc: Cosmologists discuss their project to create a map of everything in existence, and reveal that their research has yielded some highly unexpected results, creating a picture stranger than anything they had imagined. Scientists also explain why the map suggests the universe may not be an all-encompassing entity - but merely the starting point for something much bigger.(n)

programme.title: Metamorphosis - The Science of Change
programme.desc: David Malone explores the processes involved in metamorphosis, the means through which one being transforms into another, and investigates why this distinctive change seems to have such a powerful grasp on the human imagination. Along the way, he highlights examples throughout the scope of historical fiction, from the epics of Ovid to the surreal short stories of Franz Kafka and the fantasy heroics of Marvel's X-Men.(n)

programme.desc: Ade Adepitan and Arthur Williams present live coverage on day three of the Games in Rio. Reigning Paralympic and world champion Hannah Cockroft goes in the T34 100m heats at the Olympic Stadium, hoping to add to her glittering array of major titles, while the women's individual 500m time-trial takes place at the Rio Olympic Velodrome, with Megan Giglia among the favourites. Ryan Taylor could be one to watch for ParalympicsGB at Fort Copacabana in the first-ever para-triathlon at the Paralympics, and highly decorated swimmer Ellie Simmonds begins her campaign in the S6 50m freestyle heats alongside 14-year-old Ellie Robinson at the Olympic Aquatics Stadium. Plus, Great Britain take on Ukraine in the men's seven-a-side football group stages at Deodoro Olympic Park. With reports from Iwan Thomas inside the Olympic Stadium.(n)

programme.title: Paralympics 2016
programme.desc: Sophie Morgan and JJ Chalmers introduce further live coverage on day three in Rio. Matt Skelhon bids to repeat his gold-medal performance from Beijing 2008 in the air rifle events at the National Shooting Centre, world number one Will Bayley is likely to feature in the men's singles table tennis quarter-finals at Riocentro Pavilion 3, and Scotland's Sammi Kinghorn goes in the 400m wheelchair heats at the Olympic Stadium.(n)

programme.desc: Using high-definition cameras attached to elephants, David Attenborough follows the day-to-day lives of four tiger cubs in India's Pench National Park. programme.desc: The cubs are now half-grown, and their games become more serious as they learn the fighting skills they will need when they are adults. David Attenborough presents.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Gibbs is forced to take a step back from work when his increasingly frail father Jackson begs him to help track down an old friend from the Second World War who does not have long left to live. Meanwhile, the rest of the team investigate the death of a marine sergeant who appears to have been caught in the crossfire during a bungled robbery, but Tony and Tim find evidence the victim may have been targeted. Crime drama, guest starring Ralph Waite (The Waltons), with Mark Harmon.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Petty officer Jody Ray is killed by a hit-and-run driver and evidence points to staff sergeant Justin Dunne, whose guilt seems certain when DiNozzo and McGee find him washing a bloodstained knife when they go to arrest him. However, Dunne tells his lawyer Carrie Clark he was miles away in Falls Church at the time - stabbing bookmaker Donny Sullivan to death. Unable to reveal the truth to the NCIS team, Clark decides to check out the alibi herself. Crime drama, guest starring Salli Richardson-Whitfield (A Town Called Eureka).(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: An internal security breach forces NCIS to go into lockdown when a covert listening device is found in a pen belonging to Secretary of the Navy Sarah Porter. DiNozzo discovers that National Security Agency analyst Ellie Bishop wrote a report two years previously predicting the possibility of such an occurrence and she is brought in to assist with the investigation and track down the culprit. Guest starring Leslie Hope and Emily Wickersham.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: The team is called in to investigate when marine corporal Flegman is found shot to death, and a phone leads them to a hotel room where Gibbs awkwardly stumbles upon his ex-wife Diane Sterling and her FBI agent ex-husband TC Fornell. She had been attempting to call her boyfriend Eddie to break up with him, but somehow Flegman had taken possession of his phone. The team tracks down Eddie's car and discovers a clown nose along with traces of blood and he quickly becomes the prime suspect.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: The team investigate when a mysterious, fast-spreading illness strikes children from military families. While Gibbs investigates the cause, Abby and Jimmy partner with the Naval Medical Research Centre in the hope of delivering a cure before the holidays. Mark Harmon stars.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Ducky is assaulted by a man who claims to have previously undisclosed information about his half-brother, who died decades ago. While his NCIS colleagues traces the attacker's whereabouts, Dr Mallard recalls the emotional final days he spent with his sibling. Elsehwhere, as the holiday season approaches, Bishop and Jake discuss the future of their relationship. Naval crime drama, starring David McCallum.(n)

programme.title: NCIS

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses

programme.desc: The stories of firefighters who served during the terrorist attacks in New York on September 11, 2001, who accounted for 343 of the 2,752 dead. Their bold tactic of rushing into the heart of skyscraper fires cost many lives, but also saved a large number of others. This documentary speaks to survivors and the families of those who died to explore what happened on the day, and the difficulties of the years that have followed.(n)

programme.desc: Amateur footage and audiotape recorded by people around New York, giving an insight into their experiences of the September 11 terrorist attacks on the World Trade Centre in 2001. programme.title: Star Trek V: The Final Frontier
programme.desc: The Starship Enterprise races to the rescue of intergalactic ambassadors held hostage on a distant planet. Sci-fi adventure, written, directed by and starring William Shatner, with Leonard Nimoy, DeForest Kelley and David Warner.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek VI: The Undiscovered Country
programme.desc: Captain Kirk is framed for the assassination of the Klingon head of state just as the Federation is about to make peace with their old enemies. As Kirk and Dr McCoy are banished to an icy prison planet, Spock tries to uncover the identity of the real killers. Sci-fi adventure sequel, with William Shatner, Leonard Nimoy, DeForest Kelley, Christopher Plummer, with appearances by Christian Slater and Michael Dorn from Star Trek: The Next Generation.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: Generations
programme.desc: USS Enterprise Captain Jean-Luc Picard must stop a deranged genius obsessed with gaining access to a mysterious energy source - regardless of the threat to entire civilisations that lie in his path. Help arrives from an unlikely quarter - his supposedly long dead predecessor Captain James T Kirk. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring Patrick Stewart, William Shatner, Malcolm McDowell and Whoopi Goldberg.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: First Contact
programme.desc: Captain Jean-Luc Picard and the crew of the Enterprise face their deadliest enemies, the Borg, who travel back in time in an attempt to change Earth's history. The starship follows on a mission to foil their plan, but the vessel is taken over by members of the cyborg collective, leaving Picard consumed by a desire for revenge. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring Patrick Stewart, Jonathan Frakes, Brent Spiner, James Cromwell and Alice Krige.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: Insurrection
programme.desc: Captain Picard and the Enterprise crew uncover a conspiracy by their own superiors and a sinister alien race to take over a peaceful world and exploit its power to prolong life. However, the crew is forced to defy Federation orders and turns renegade to protect the planet's inhabitants. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring Patrick Stewart, F Murray Abraham, Jonathan Frakes, Brent Spiner and Michael Dorn.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: Nemesis
programme.desc: The crew of the Starship Enterprise is sent to form an alliance with old enemies the Romulans after the alien empire is taken over by a new leader - a clone of Captain Picard. Though claiming to want peace, Starfleet's finest soon realise he has more sinister plans in mind, involving a doomsday weapon that could destroy Earth. Sci-fi adventure, starring Patrick Stewart, Tom Hardy and Brent Spiner.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek
programme.desc: The trainee crew members of the starship Enterprise embark on their maiden flight, which pits them against a Romulan commander from the future who is planning a horrific revenge on those he blames for a tragedy in his own time. Sci-fi adventure based on the original TV series, starring Chris Pine, Zachary Quinto, Eric Bana, Zoe Saldana and Leonard Nimoy.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: The Motion Picture
programme.desc: A mysterious, planet-sized energy cloud is heading for Earth, destroying everything in its path. Admiral James T Kirk returns to the bridge of the Enterprise to stop the invader, but he has to contend with a bitter rival and the possession of one of his crew by the alien force. Sci-fi adventure, the first movie based on the TV series, starring William Shatner, Leonard Nimoy, DeForest Kelley and Persis Khambatta.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan
programme.desc: The Enterprise crew faces a bitter battle to the death with an old enemy. Khan, a genetically engineered superhuman tyrant, has escaped exile on a barren planet and hijacked a starship to take his revenge on Admiral Kirk, while also scheming to turn an experimental planet-creating device into a doomsday weapon. Sci-fi adventure sequel, with William Shatner, Leonard Nimoy, Ricardo Montalban and Kirstie Alley.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek III: The Search for Spock
programme.desc: Admiral Kirk and his crew hijack the decommissioned Enterprise to recover the body of their fallen comrade Mr Spock from the planet Genesis. Kirk has learnt that Spock's spirit is still alive, and the Vulcan can be resurrected, but he must also battle a Klingon captain determined to control the planet's mysterious energy. Sci-fi sequel, directed by Leonard Nimoy, with William Shatner, DeForest Kelley and Christopher Lloyd.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek IV: The Voyage Home
programme.desc: The Enterprise crew travels back in time to prevent an alien probe destroying the Earth. The only thing that can avert the disaster is a humpback whale, a creature extinct in the 23rd century - but adjusting to life back in 1986 proves a distinct challenge. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring William Shatner, DeForest Kelley and Leonard Nimoy, who also directed.(n)
